# CMake and vcpkg (Cursor rule)

- Visible configure/build presets must inherit `normalized-configure-environment` / `normalized-build-environment` (see `tools/check-toolchain.ps1` and `AGENTS.md`).
- After manual `git worktree add`, run `pwsh -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File tools/prepare-worktree.ps1` inside the linked worktree before configure.
- Install optional packages only via `pwsh -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File tools/bootstrap-deps.ps1`. CMake configure stays on `VCPKG_MANIFEST_INSTALL=OFF` and `VCPKG_INSTALLED_DIR=${sourceDir}/vcpkg_installed`.
- Do not delete `external/vcpkg`; restore with `git clone https://github.com/microsoft/vcpkg.git external/vcpkg` then bootstrap when missing.
- MSVC targets must keep bounded `/MP2` plus `/Zf`, per-target `COMPILE_PDB_OUTPUT_DIRECTORY` / `COMPILE_PDB_NAME`, and linkable-target `/INCREMENTAL:NO` through `MK_apply_common_target_options`; use `tools/cmake.ps1` so stale `.tlog` directories with older aliased `.lastbuildstate` roots are cleared before Visual Studio builds, and do not add global `/FS` for C1041 unless a measured follow-up proves it is still required.
- `tools/validate.ps1` prepares CMake File API codemodel data before its single `build.ps1` configure/build, reuses that reply for the clang-tidy smoke unless `-SkipTidySmoke` is explicitly passed, and runs CTest through `test.ps1 -SkipBuild`; standalone wrappers keep conservative defaults.
- **`MK_tools`:** cluster `OBJECT` targets under `engine/tools/{shader,gltf,asset,scene}/`; see [`docs/specs/2026-05-11-directory-layout-target-v1.md`](../../docs/specs/2026-05-11-directory-layout-target-v1.md).
